history.content: Grad sections of mezzanine courses are always waitlist-only until near the beginning of the offered semester. These grad sections of undergraduate courses were created and are prioritized for EECS masters students. Once those students have been accommodated, it is up to the instructor of those courses to set a balance for the remaining seats between the undergrad and grad sections and to prioritize enrollment among students who remain on the grad section waitlist.
Why are all grad students put on the CS289A waitlist while undergrads could enroll in CS189? Are some spaces being saved for grad students?
history.subject: How will registration for CS289A Work?
